# The Seven Commandments · the law, rewritten

a distilled thread of ANIMAL FARM — a member of the NOUTHESIA universe of warnings. emergence: spiritual. moniker ⟦The Seven Commandments:AFM:993120⟧

**who —** The Seven Commandments — the laws of Animalism painted on the barn, reduced over time to a single line.
**what —** The measure of the betrayal: each commandment is quietly amended (‘…without cause,’ ‘…in sheets,’ ‘…to excess’) until only ‘some more equal’ remains.
**where —** On the end wall of the big barn.
**why —** Because you can chart a tyranny by what it does to its own founding law — and here the law is edited in the dark.
**how —** By Squealer's nocturnal paint-pot, altering the wall faster than memory can hold the original.

**the seal —** I began as seven honest laws and ended as one obscene line — and no one could ever quite prove I'd been changed.

